<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Stepping Hill Hospital is located just off the A6, approx 2 miles south of Stockport town centre.  Travelling to the hospital has never been easier, due to excellent bus and train services.  Transport leaflet racks are located near the entrance to each Outpatient Dept and Oak House/ Main entrance. For further travel information telephone 0161 228 7811 between 8am and 8pm, seven days a week.  Regular bus services bring you directly into the hospital grounds. Please click on the transport website for more details.


</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There are Pay &amp; Display car parks at the hospital. Parking is limited so please leave yourself more time in case you need to search for a space. Parking charges are £3.50 for 0-2 hours, £5.50 for 2-4 hours or £8.00 for all day. Please do not park on the road as this can obstruct emergency vehicles. Disabled car parking spaces are free of charge, however a valid blue badge must be clearly displayed.</p>
